Caramelized Onion Dip
  --Cook's Illustrated

1 c sour cream
2/3 caramelized onions, chopped fine
1/3 c yogurt
2 tbsp minced fresh chives
3/4 tsp white vinegar
1/2 table salt
1/8 tsp black pepper

Stir together all ingredients. Refrigerate for 1 hrs. Adjust seasoning as needed. Serve.



Caramelized Onions

3 lbs onions, halved and sliced through root end 1/4" thick
13 tbsp water (3/4 c + 1 tbsp)
2 tbsp vegetable oil
3/4 tsp salt
1/8 tsp baking soda

Bring onions, 3/4 c water, oil, and salt to boil in 12" nonstick skillet over high heat. Cover and cookuntil water has evaporated and onions start to sizzle, ~10 min. Uncover, reduce heat to medium high, and use robber spatula to gently press onions into sides and bottom of skillet. Cook, without stirring, for 30 s. Stir onions, scraping fond from skillet, then gently press onions into sides and bottom again. Repeat pressing, cooking, and stirring until onions are softened, well browned, and slightly sticky, 15-20 min. Combine baking soda and remaining 1 tbsp water in bowl. Stir solution into onions and cook, stirring constantly, until solution has evaporated, ~1 min. Transfer onions to bowl. Can be kept in refrigerator for 3 days or frozen for up to 1 month. Makes ~2 c.

Notes: preference is yellow or spanish onions
